    Dispose Graphics2D in try/finally in BackgroundBlendFilter (#656)

    In BackgroundBlendFilter.apply the Graphics2D was disposed
    unconditionally after setComposite/drawImage. If either call threw,
    dispose() would be skipped, leaking the native graphics context. Wrap
    the drawing in try { ... } finally { g.dispose(); } to match every
    other filter in this package (BorderFilter, ColorizeFilter,
    VintageFilter, WatermarkFilter, etc.). Pure resource-safety fix with no
    behaviour change on the happy path.

