    Don't leak temp frame file when write fails in StreamingWebpWriter (#699)

    In WebpStream.writeFrame, Files.createTempFile succeeded and then
    Files.write could throw (disk full, permissions) before the temp Path
    was added to the inputs list that close() iterates for cleanup, so the
    scrimage_webp_frame_* file leaked on disk. Delete the temp file and
    rethrow if the write fails; deleting (rather than registering first)
    also keeps inputs and delays in sync if the caller swallows the
    exception and carries on.

    Adds regression tests pinning that no scrimage temp files remain after
    a normal write+close, and that the buffered frame files are cleaned up
    when close() fails writing to the destination stream.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
