    Dispose javax ImageWriter via finally spanning all uses in GifWriter.write (#657)

    The native javax.imageio.ImageWriter was acquired, then getDefaultWriteParam(),
    canWriteProgressive() and setProgressiveMode() ran outside the try/finally that
    disposes the writer. If any of those param calls threw a RuntimeException (e.g.
    from a writer plugin), writer.dispose() was never called and the native GIF
    writer's resources leaked.

    Move the `try {` to immediately after acquiring the writer so the outermost
    finally { writer.dispose(); } spans every use, mirroring the fixes already
    applied to JpegWriter.write and PngWriter.write. Pure resource-leak hardening
    with no behavior change on the success path.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
