    Replace disabled-by-default assert range checks in HSLColor with explicit validation (#666)

    The HSLColor(hue, saturation, lightness, alpha) constructor validated its
    arguments with Java `assert` statements, which are disabled by default in
    production JVMs. Out-of-range components were therefore stored unchecked and
    silently produced wrong colours when later converted via toRGB().

    Replace the four asserts with explicit IllegalArgumentException checks
    (hue in [0,360], saturation/lightness/alpha in [0,1]), matching the active
    pattern already used in RGBColor and the VignetteFilter cleanup (30ac7fe9).
    The constructor signature is unchanged.

