    Validate Grayscale gray/alpha range at construction (mirror RGBColor) (#678)

    Grayscale's two-arg constructor stored gray and alpha unchecked, unlike
    RGBColor which validates each component is in [0,255] and throws
    IllegalArgumentException. An out-of-range value (e.g. gray=300, alpha=-1)
    was accepted silently and only failed later inside toRGB() when wrapped in
    an RGBColor, turning a clear construction-site error into a confusing
    deferred failure.

    Add the same explicit requireInRange validation for gray and alpha in the
    constructor to fail fast with a clear message, matching the proven RGBColor
    pattern. Also add the missing @Override to toRGB(), which implements
    Color.toRGB() (RGBColor and the GrayscaleMethod implementations already
    annotate it).

