    vboxFromPixels scanned each channel with `if (v < min) ... else if (v > max)`.
    Because min starts at 1000000 and max at 0, the first pixel always takes the
    `< min` branch and never updates max. For an image that is monochrome in a
    channel (a single distinct quantized value v), that channel ends up with
    min = v and max = 0, i.e. min > max. VBox.volume() then computes a negative
    volume and VBox.count() iterates an empty range, so the colour dimension is
    silently dropped from the median-cut quantization.

    Use independent if's so both bounds update from every pixel.

