Author: Sam <sam@sksamuel.com>
Date:   Thu May 28 23:06:12 2026 -0500

    Fix contributor-buffer overflow in ResampleOp sub-sampling (#514)

    createSubSampling allocated numContributors = (int)(width*2 + 2) slots per
    destination row/column, but the actual sample window for a destination pixel
    is [floor(center - width), ceil(center + width)], whose size is
    ceil(center+width) - floor(center-width) + 1 and can reach ceil(2*width) + 2.
    The truncating "+2" pad was one short for certain scale factors, so the final
    contributor was written at arrPixel[subindex + numContributors], spilling into
    the next destination row/column's segment (and polluting its weight
    normalisation), corrupting both.

    Verified: resampling a 121px axis to 3px with the Triangle filter produced
    corrupted output on the old code; with the window-derived size the output is
    correct, and resampling output for all non-overflowing size/filter
    combinations is byte-identical to before (the extra slots carry zero weight
    and are never read, since the consumers iterate only up to arrN[i]).

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
