Author: Sam <sam@sksamuel.com>
Date:   Thu May 28 22:46:40 2026 -0500

    Add RepeaterFilter that tiles the image into a larger grid (#547)

    RepeaterFilter(columns, rows) produces a new image columns times the
    source width and rows times the source height, drawing the source at
    full size into every cell. RepeaterFilter(2, 3) therefore yields a 2x3
    tiling that is twice as wide and three times as tall as the original.

    Because it changes the image dimensions it is implemented as a Transform
    (applied via image.transform(...)) rather than a size-preserving Filter.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
