Author: Sam <sam@sksamuel.com>
Date:   Thu May 28 22:17:01 2026 -0500

    Clamp channels in OpacityFilter to prevent bit-bleed (#518)

    OpacityFilter computes each channel as r + (255 - r) * amount and packs the
    result with nr << 16 etc. without masking or clamping. For amount inside [0, 1]
    the values stay in range, but amount > 1 (or < 0) pushes a channel above 255
    (or negative); shifted unmasked it overflows into the neighbouring channel's
    bits and produces an arbitrary corrupted colour instead of a saturated one.

    Clamp each channel to [0, 255]. This is a no-op for the normal [0, 1] amount
    range and saturates gracefully otherwise, matching how PixelTools.scale and
    other filters in this package were hardened.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
