    Back subpixelSubimage with one cached interpolator + bulk pixel read (#536)

    subpixelSubimage called the inherited subpixel(x, y) once per output
    cell, and each call constructed a new LinearSubpixelInterpolator that
    then issued up to four scalar BufferedImage.getRGB(x, y) calls. For an
    NxM extraction that is N*M interpolator allocations and up to 4*N*M
    scalar colour-model conversions.

    - Add a LinearSubpixelInterpolator(AwtImage, int[] pixels) constructor
      that reads neighbours from a pre-supplied row-major ARGB buffer; the
      existing single-arg constructor passes null and keeps the on-demand
      scalar getRGB behaviour, so one-off AwtImage.subpixel() calls are
      unaffected (no regression for that path).
    - subpixelSubimage now does one bulk getRGB of the whole source and
      reuses a single interpolator across the loop.

    Neighbour values are identical: pixels[yc*width+xc] is exactly what
    getRGB(xc, yc) returns given the row-major bulk layout, so output pixels
    are unchanged.

