Author: Sam <sam@sksamuel.com>
Date:   Thu May 28 21:14:34 2026 -0500

    Validate RGBColor components at runtime instead of via assert (#527)

    The constructor checked 0 <= component <= 255 with assert, which is disabled by
    default in production JVMs. An out-of-range component was therefore stored
    unchecked and later silently wrapped by `& 0xFF` in toARGBInt() — red = 256
    became 0, red = -1 became 255 — producing a wrong colour rather than failing.

    Throw IllegalArgumentException for out-of-range components. All internal
    constructions stay in range (masked ARGB ints, convex averages, and
    [0,1]-domain * 255 rounding), verified by running 2,000,000 random
    RGB/HSL/HSV/CMYK round-trips and averages with no false positives.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
