    Make X11Colorlist colour constants final (#496)

    All 658 public static RGBColor entries were declared without `final`,
    so any caller could reassign them and corrupt shared state JVM-wide
    (e.g. `X11Colorlist.Red = X11Colorlist.Black` would poison every
    consumer that later read Red).

    Adding `final` is binary-compatible for read access and only forbids
    external reassignment.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
