    Validate PngWriter compression level in the constructor (#504)

    * Validate PngWriter compression level in the constructor

    PngWriter deferred compression-level validation to write(), so an
    invalid level both produced a confusing late IOException AND, when
    the caller had opened a FileOutputStream before passing it in,
    leaked that stream until GC (write() throws before reaching the
    try-with-resources).

    Validate in the constructor so the misuse fails fast before any
    IO resources are allocated by the caller.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

    * Fix PngWriterTest assertions for constructor-level validation

    The two "invalid compression level …" cases were doing
    `original.bytes(PngWriter(-1))` and asserting the message via
    `shouldBe`. Two follow-up problems after moving validation into
    the constructor:

    1. Validation now fires before write(), so the `original.bytes(...)`
       wrapper is unreachable — call the constructor directly.
    2. The new message includes the offending value (e.g. ", got -1")
       to aid diagnostics. Switch to `shouldStartWith` so the assertion
       pins the meaningful prefix without coupling to formatting of
       the suffix.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

