    Make RandomPainter seedable and stop reseeding per tile (#508)

    RandomPainter built `new Random()` inside getRaster() — which the
    AWT renderer calls once per device tile of a draw. Net effect:

    - Output was non-reproducible across runs.
    - Adjacent tiles spawning in the same millisecond shared a seed and
      produced correlated/seamed patterns.

    Allocate the RNG once per paint() (i.e. once per draw) and add an
    optional `Long seed` constructor for full determinism.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
