    Honour SparkleFilter's (x, y) constructor parameters (#482)

    The wrapper used to call `op.setDimensions(x, y)` to pass the sparkle
    centre into jhlabs, but jhlabs' PointFilter.filter() immediately calls
    `setDimensions(srcWidth, srcHeight)` before iterating pixels — which
    unconditionally resets `centreX = width/2; centreY = height/2`. The
    wrapper's (x, y) was therefore dead, and every SparkleFilter sparkled
    at the image centre regardless of the constructor arguments.

    Add public `setCentreX` / `setCentreY` on the jhlabs SparkleFilter, then
    override `setDimensions` in an anonymous subclass inside the wrapper to
    re-apply the user-supplied centre after super resets it. (0, 0) remains
    a sentinel meaning "image centre" so the no-arg `SparkleFilter()` ctor
    preserves its long-standing default behaviour.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
