    Fix AwtImage.patches off-by-one dropping rightmost col and bottom row (#444)

    patches() enumerated (height - patchHeight) * (width - patchWidth)
    patches and looped col < width - patchWidth. For sliding-window
    enumeration, a patch starting at (col, row) is valid as long as
    col + patchWidth <= width and row + patchHeight <= height — so the
    correct count is (width - patchWidth + 1) * (height - patchHeight + 1).

    The previous formula silently dropped the rightmost column and bottom
    row of patch starts. Concretely, patches(1, 1) on a 4x4 image returned
    9 patches instead of 16: a per-pixel sweep was missing 7 pixels.

