    Validate frame index in AnimatedGif accessors (#464)

    AnimatedGif.getFrame / getDelay / getDisposeMethod passed the index
    straight through to GifSequenceReader, which silently produced wrong
    data or NPEs for an out-of-bounds frame index:

      - getFrame(n) wrapped the null result of reader.getFrame(n) in
        ImmutableImage.wrapAwt → AwtImage's `assert awt != null` is a
        no-op in production, then awt.getWidth() NPE'd on the next pixel
        access
      - getDelay returned Duration.ofMillis(-1), a negative duration
        with no indication that the index was bad
      - getDisposeMethod silently returned NONE

    Add an upfront index check that throws IndexOutOfBoundsException
    naming the bad index and the available frame count. This matches
    what AnimatedWebp's underlying List.get already throws.

    Add AnimatedGifBoundsTest with four cases (negative, == frameCount,
    above frameCount, negative on getDisposeMethod). All four fail on
    master with NPE / silent wrong data; all four pass after the fix.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
