commit 2d86f67bcd62788f3c55f4c51c8013d69851298b
Author: Sam <sam@sksamuel.com>
Date:   Fri May 1 22:23:36 2026 -0500

    Add AnimatedWebp reader using anim_dump and webpmux (#449)

    Animated WebP analogue of AnimatedGif / AnimatedGifReader: read an
    animated WebP from any ImageSource and decompose it into per-frame
    ImmutableImages plus canvas size, loop count and per-frame display
    durations.

    Frames are extracted via libwebp's `anim_dump`, which renders each
    frame with disposal and blending already applied — so getFrame(n)
    returns the final composed image rather than the raw inter-frame
    patch. Per-frame metadata (durations, loop count, canvas size) is
    parsed out of `webpmux -info`.

      AnimatedWebp animated = AnimatedWebpReader.read(ImageSource.of(file));
      int n = animated.getFrameCount();
      ImmutableImage frame0 = animated.getFrame(0);
      Duration delay0 = animated.getDelay(0);

    Two new thin handlers wrap the binaries: AnimDumpHandler and
    WebpMuxHandler. WebpMuxHandler exposes a small parsed view
    (WebpInfo + FrameInfo records) of the `-info` output. Both use the
    same lookup chain as the existing webp handlers (system property →
    classpath /webp_binaries/ → bundled binaries) and trigger their
    static install when AnimatedWebpReader is first referenced.

    Bundle anim_dump and webpmux for the same five platforms scrimage
    already ships cwebp / dwebp / gif2webp / img2webp on:
    linux-x86-64, linux-aarch64, mac-x86-64, mac-arm64, windows-x64.

    Tests:
    - read the existing /animated.webp fixture and pin canvas (648x648),
      frame count (34), loop count (0), and per-frame delay (30 ms)
    - assert each rendered frame matches the canvas dimensions
    - preserve the original webp bytes via getBytes()
    - round-trip three distinct frames through StreamingWebpWriter and
      read them back, verifying frame count, mixed delays, and that the
      rendered frames carry the correct dominant colour
    - unit-test WebpMuxHandler.parseInfo against a representative info dump

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
