Author: Sam <sam@sksamuel.com>
Date:   Fri May 1 22:03:20 2026 -0500

    Hand-code hashCode for Grayscale/CMYK/HSL/HSV to avoid varargs boxing (#402)

    * Hand-code hashCode for Grayscale/CMYK/HSL/HSV to avoid varargs boxing

    Companion to the RGBColor/Pixel hand-coded hashCode change. Same
    Objects.hash(varargs...) issue: each call allocates a fresh boxed
    Object[] (with each int auto-boxed to Integer, each float to Float).

    Replace with the standard 31 * hash + field pattern:
    - Grayscale (two int fields): 31 * gray + alpha
    - CMYK / HSL / HSV (float fields): 31 * hash + Float.floatToIntBits(field)

    These types are less hot than RGBColor but the change is mechanical and
    keeps the convention uniform across all Color subclasses.

    * Add hashCode contract tests for Grayscale/CMYK/HSL/HSV

    Pin down for each color type:
    - equal objects produce equal hash codes (the contract that matters)
    - hash codes differ when any single field differs (the 31*hash+field
      pattern over 2-5 small values does discriminate cleanly)

    These tests would catch any future regression that breaks the contract
    (equal but unequal hashes) or accidentally collapses distinct values
    to the same hash.
