    Fast-path AwtImage color queries to int comparisons (#391)

    * Fast-path AwtImage color queries to int comparisons

    contains(Color), count(Color), and isFilled(Color) all reduced to a
    packed-ARGB int comparison, but the implementations forced a Pixel[]
    materialisation and per-pixel allocation: contains/isFilled wrapped
    the predicate around p.toARGBInt() / p.argb, count(Color) went
    further and built an RGBColor per pixel just to call equals().

    Inline a single bulk getRGB read and compare against color.getRGB()
    directly. Same packed-ARGB layout on both sides, so behaviour is
    preserved; allocations drop to one int[] regardless of image size.

    * Add tests for the color-query int-comparison fast paths

    contains(Color), count(Color), and isFilled(Color) are now packed-ARGB
    int comparisons against a bulk getRGB read. Pin behaviour with focused
    tests:

    - contains: returns true on a match, false otherwise, and is alpha-aware
      (a fully opaque pixel must NOT be reported as containing the same RGB
      in a semi-transparent variant)
    - count: returns the exact number of pixels with a fully matching ARGB
    - isFilled: true iff every pixel matches; false if even one differs

    These would catch any regression that confuses the packed-int form for
    something else (e.g., dropping the alpha bits, or comparing a
    materialised Pixel/RGBColor that loses alpha along the way).
