Author: Sam <sam@sksamuel.com>
Date:   Fri May 1 21:42:03 2026 -0500

    Add Img2WebpHandler for animated WebP from frame images (#446)

    Mirrors Gif2WebpHandler but wraps libwebp's `img2webp` tool, which
    encodes a sequence of input frames (PNG / JPEG / TIFF / PNM / WebP)
    into a single animated WebP. This complements gif2webp for callers
    who already have rendered frames (e.g. produced by scrimage) and
    don't want to round-trip through GIF first.

    The handler accepts an in-memory list of frame bytes (or a list of
    paths), plus the standard knobs: per-frame delay, loop count, RGB
    quality, encoding method, and a lossless flag. Emit per-frame
    options before each frame so the call is unambiguous regardless of
    frame count.

    Reuse the existing WebpHandler installation machinery so the binary
    can come from `com.sksamuel.scrimage.webp.binary.dir`, the
    classpath-overridable `/webp_binaries/img2webp`, or the bundled
    `/dist_webp_binaries/libwebp-1.4.0-<platform>/bin/img2webp` for
    linux-x86-64, linux-aarch64, mac-x86-64, mac-arm64 and windows-x64.

    Add Img2WebpHandlerTest with three cases that drive the bundled
    binary end-to-end: default options, explicit options, and the
    empty-input-list precondition.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
