    Fix ImmutableImage.filter() mutating the original image in place (#364)

    When filter.types() is empty (the default), filter() assigned target = this
    and then called filter.apply(target). BufferedOpFilter.apply() calls
    op().filter(image.awt(), image.awt()), which modifies the image's pixel
    buffer in place. The "immutable" original was therefore silently mutated,
    violating the documented contract: "The original (this) image is unchanged."

    Fix: always copy before applying — copy() when the type matches, copy(type)
    when a conversion is needed.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
