    Fix Color.average() returning premultiplied-alpha values as straight-alpha (#358)

    The Porter-Duff compositing formula computes premultiplied RGB values
    (c1.red * a1 + c2.red * a2 * (1 - a1)). When the output alpha is less
    than 1, these must be divided by aOut to convert back to straight-alpha
    before storing in RGBColor. Without this, partially-transparent blends
    produce RGB channels that are too dark.

    Added regression tests covering opaque, transparent, and semi-transparent
    blend cases, including a case showing the old incorrect premultiplied value
    vs. the correct normalized value.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
