    Fix dead validation and resource leak in PngWriter (#356)

    Two bugs:
    1. Compression-level validation used && instead of ||, making the
       condition impossible to satisfy (a value cannot simultaneously
       be < 0 AND >= 10). Invalid levels were silently accepted.
       Fixed to use ||.

    2. ImageOutputStream and ImageWriter were closed via straight-line
       calls with no try/finally, so any exception during write() left
       them open. Fixed with try-with-resources for the stream and a
       finally block for writer.dispose(), matching the pattern used
       in TwelveMonkeysWriter.

    Co-authored-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
