    Add ImmutableImageLoader.fromTorchTensor() for CHW tensor data (#355)

    * Add ImmutableImageLoader.fromTorchTensor() for CHW tensor data

    Adds two overloads to ImmutableImageLoader:
    - fromTorchTensor(int[], width, height)  — values 0-255
    - fromTorchTensor(float[], width, height) — values 0.0-1.0

    Both accept flat arrays in PyTorch CHW (channel, height, width) order
    and support 1-channel (grayscale), 3-channel (RGB), and 4-channel (RGBA)
    tensors. Out-of-range values are clamped to 0-255. The resulting image
    type respects the loader's type() setting and defaults to TYPE_INT_ARGB
    for 4-channel tensors and TYPE_INT_RGB otherwise.

    Closes #318

